All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actor
    Represents a specific type of MoviePeople: Actor or Actress.
    Admin
    Represents a staff who has access to the editing system
    App
    Represents the whole MOBLIMA App
    BaseController
    Generally represents a controller that is able to perform a specific task This is the superclass of all classes under controller folder
    BaseEntity
    This is the superclass / baseclass of all the other classes under modules.entity package
    BookingHistoryController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to list out booking histories of a user specified by email
    Cineplex
    Represents a cineplex which contains multiple cinemas
    ConsoleUI
    Represents an user interface that manages input and output through the console It is instantiated when entering the app and passed down by controllers.
    DataBase
    Represents a data base that is able to read and write data from the txt files under dataFiles folder.
    Director
    Represents a specific type of MoviePeople: Director.
    GeneralEnter
    This is to be implemented by controllers that specifically work for admin or common user
    Holiday
    Represents a day that is recognized as public holiday
    ListCineplexController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to list out all cineplexs
    ListMovieController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to list out movie names in consoleUI
    ListMovieInfoController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to display movie information details differently for admin or customer
    ListShowController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to list out show plans for a specific movie in a specific cineplex for common user, or all valid show plans for staff
    ListShowInfoController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to list out detailed show information for common users to confirm before proceeding to booking, or for staff to choose from to edit.
    LoginProcessController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to do log in for an admin
    Movie
    Represents a movie
    MovieGoner
    Represents a movie-goner that has gone through the ticket booking process
    MoviePeople
    Represents a people who is either a director or actor/actress
    MovieRankingController
    Represents a router page which allows a user to choose in which way the movie list shall be sorted and is able to proceed to the listing after choosing
    MovieReviewingController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to get new review from the user and store them back to txt file
    Review
    Represents a Review by a movie-goner that contains rating and comments A Review is specific to one movie
    RunApp
    Represents a wrapper to run or restart the App.
    Show
    Represents a show or, in another word, a movie session inside a cinema of a cineplex
    Sorting
    This class is modified lab4 manual and reused here for movie ranking function
    StaffMenuController
    Represents a router page which provides all available admin action options and is able to proceed to the corresponding functions after choosing
    Ticket
    Represents a ticket to a show (for one seat)
    TicketingController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to make booking according to the user's request
    TicketType
    Represents a type of ticket which ticket prices depend on
    UpdateMovieController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to do manipulation on Movie object.
    UpdateShowController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to do manipulation on Show object.
    UpdateSystemController
    Represents a type of controller that is able to do manipulation on system configuration.
    UserMenuController
    Represents a router page which provides all available Movie-goner action options and is able to proceed to the corresponding functions after the choosing
    UserSelectingController
    Represents the homepage which appears after the entry of the App.
    WithAdminEnter
    This is to be implemented by controllers that performs differently for admin and common user
